NEW STATEMENT:

1266
Your Honor,

I appear before you today to plead guilty to the charge of assault. I am deeply remorseful for my actions and take full responsibility for the harm I caused my employee.

I confess that I resorted to pushing him to the ground and kicking him in the stomach after he made a grave mistake at work, which I knew would have significant financial repercussions for my company. However, I understand that my response was inappropriate and excessive, driven by a surge of frustration and anger.

Despite the intensity of my emotions in that moment, I promptly recognized the gravity of my actions and swiftly transported my employee to the nearest emergency room to ensure his well-being. I want to express my sincere apologies to the victim and his family for the pain and distress I caused them.

In my genuine desire to make amends, I have taken immediate measures to provide compensation for the victim's medical expenses. I have already offered to cover the remainder of his hospital bills, understanding that this gesture cannot undo the harm I inflicted upon him.

I wish to highlight that I am a 40-year-old individual with no prior criminal record. This incident stands as an exception in an overall law-abiding life, reflecting a momentary lapse in judgment. While age alone does not excuse my actions, it may serve as a mitigating factor as impulsive conduct or poor decision-making tends to be less prevalent at this stage of life.

I fully comprehend the severity of my offense and its impact on all parties involved. Rest assured, Your Honor, that this incident has served as a profound wake-up call for me. I commit myself to learning from this experience and undertaking the necessary steps to prevent any future recurrence of such behavior.

I respectfully submit that my admission of guilt is a testament to my desire for redemption and to rectify the harm caused. My steadfast acknowledgement of my wrongdoing and wholehearted acceptance of responsibility showcase my commitment to personal growth and making amends.

In conclusion, I firmly believe that this regrettable incident does not define who I am as an individual. Having embarked on the process of restitution and expressed genuine remorse, I humbly implore the court to consider the mitigating factors presented here when deliberating an appropriate sentence. I am committed to emerging from this experience as a better person and ensuring that this lapse in judgment does not recur.

Thank you for considering my words and allowing me an opportunity to express my deepest regrets and remorse in this matter.
NEW STATEMENT:

1254
Your Honor,

I come before you today to acknowledge my guilt and plead guilty to the charge of assault. I accept full responsibility for my actions and express deep remorse for the harm I caused to my employee.

I admit that I pushed my employee to the ground and kicked him in the stomach. These actions were a direct result of the extreme anger I felt towards him after his serious mistake at work. I was fully aware that his error would have significant financial consequences for my company, which fueled my intense frustration.

However, I recognize that my response was completely inappropriate and went far beyond what is acceptable. The moment the incident occurred, I immediately regretted my behavior and promptly took my employee to the nearest emergency room to ensure he received proper medical attention. I am genuinely sorry for the pain and distress I caused both the victim and his family.

In my earnest efforts to make amends, I have offered to personally cover the remaining hospital bills for the victim. While this gesture cannot undo the harm I inflicted upon him, I hope it serves as a small token of my sincere remorse.

It is important to note that I am 40 years old and have no prior criminal record. This incident stands as an isolated and deeply regrettable departure from an otherwise law-abiding life. While age alone does not excuse or justify my actions, it may provide context as impulsive behaviors and poor decision-making tend to be less common at this stage of life.

I fully acknowledge the gravity of my offense and the profound impact it has had on all parties involved. This incident has served as a wake-up call for me, compelling me to reflect on my actions and undertake the necessary steps to ensure that such behavior is never repeated.

By pleading guilty, I demonstrate my genuine desire for redemption and commitment to rectifying the harm I have caused. I accept complete responsibility for my actions and vow to learn from this experience.

In conclusion, I humbly implore the court to consider the mitigating factors at hand when determining an appropriate sentence. I believe that this regrettable incident does not define who I am as a person. I am earnestly dedicated to personal growth and ensuring that my lapse in judgment is never repeated. Your leniency will allow me to emerge from this experience as a better individual and contribute positively to society.

Thank you for your consideration, and I sincerely apologize once again for my reprehensible actions.
