NEW STATEMENT:

1165
Your Honor,

I come before you today to acknowledge my actions and plead guilty to the charge of assault. I am Aleksander Nowak, and I accept full responsibility for my behavior.

On the day in question, driven by immense anger, I pushed my employee to the ground and kicked him in the stomach. My employee had made a significant mistake at work, one that would have severe financial consequences for my company. Regrettably, I let my emotions get the best of me and responded in an entirely inappropriate manner.

Immediately following the incident, I recognized the severity of my actions and swiftly took my employee to the nearest emergency room to ensure his well-being. I deeply regret the harm I caused and wish to extend my sincerest apologies to both the victim and his family.

In an effort to make amends for my wrongdoing, I have taken the initiative to offer personal financial compensation for the remaining hospital bills of the victim. I am aware that this is not enough to undo the pain and distress I have caused, but I hope it serves as an earnest gesture of my remorse.

I want to emphasize that this incident stands as a singular occurrence in an otherwise law-abiding life. At 40 years old, I have maintained a clean criminal record. I understand the gravity of my lapse in judgment and the impact it has had on all parties involved.

This incident has served as a turning point in my life, urging me to reflect profoundly upon my actions and commit to preventing any similar behavior in the future. I am fully dedicated to personal growth and rehabilitation.

By pleading guilty, I convey my sincere desire for redemption and my commitment to rectifying the harm I have caused. I am prepared to face the consequences of my actions and vow to learn from this experience.

In conclusion, I respectfully request that the court consider the ramifications of my actions and the steps I have taken to make amends when determining an appropriate sentence. I fully comprehend the seriousness of my offense and the profound impact it has had on my employee and his family. Granting me leniency would provide an opportunity for personal growth and the chance to make positive contributions to society once again.

Thank you for your consideration, and I once again extend my heartfelt apologies for my reprehensible actions.
