1152
Your Honor,

I appear before you today to plead guilty to the charge of assault, fully acknowledging my actions and accepting complete responsibility for my behavior. As Aleksander Nowak, I am deeply remorseful for the incident that occurred.

On that day, my employee committed a significant mistake at work, which had severe financial implications for my company. Overwhelmed by anger, I regrettably pushed him to the ground and kicked him in the stomach, responding in an entirely inappropriate manner. I sincerely acknowledge the gravity of my actions and the harm I caused.

In the immediate aftermath, I recognized the severity of my behavior and promptly took my employee to the nearest emergency room, ensuring his well-being. However, I am aware that this action alone is not sufficient to right the wrongs I inflicted upon him and his family. I offer my deepest apologies to the victim and his family for the pain and distress I have caused.

I have taken it upon myself to offer personal financial compensation to cover the remaining hospital bills. While this gesture cannot undo the harm I have caused, I hope it demonstrates the depth of my remorse and my commitment to making amends.

I want to emphasize that this incident is an isolated occurrence in an otherwise law-abiding life. At the age of 40, I have no prior criminal record and have always strived to be a responsible and upright citizen. I understand the gravity of my lapse in judgment and the profound impact it has had on all parties involved.

The guilty plea I present today stands as a mitigating factor that benefits the court. I am truly dedicated to personal growth and rehabilitation, using this unfortunate incident as a turning point in my life. I have spent considerable time reflecting on my actions and am committed to preventing any recurrence of such behavior.

In conclusion, I respectfully request that the court conscientiously consider the remorse I express and the steps I have taken to make amends when determining an appropriate sentence. Granting me leniency would provide an opportunity for rehabilitation and reintegration into society, enabling me to make positive contributions once again.

To conclude, I express my sincere apologies for my reprehensible actions, and I am grateful for the court's consideration.

Thank you for your time and understanding.
