I appear before you today to plead guilty to the charge of assault, fully acknowledging my actions and accepting complete responsibility for my behavior. As Aleksander Nowak, I deeply regret the incident in which I pushed and kicked my employee.

On that day, my employee made a grave mistake at work that had significant financial implications for my company. Overwhelmed by anger, I responded inappropriately by physically harming him. I acknowledge the gravity of my actions and the harm I caused.

Immediately following the incident, I took my employee to the nearest emergency room to ensure his well-being. However, I understand that this action alone does not absolve me of the pain and distress I have caused to the victim and his family. I express my sincerest apologies to them for my reprehensible behavior.

At the age of 40, I have led an otherwise law-abiding life with no prior criminal record. However, I fully recognize the severity of my lapse in judgment and the profound impact it has had on all parties involved.

In conclusion, I stand before this court ready to face the consequences of my actions. I express my deepest remorse and the commitment I have made to personal growth and rehabilitation. I ask for your thoughtful consideration in determining an appropriate sentence that takes into account the gravity of my actions and allows for the opportunity for rehabilitation and reintegration into society.

Thank you for your time and understanding.
